        "#Preprocessing: prepare data to train the model\n",
        "Dts = pd.read_csv(\"ai4i2020.csv\") # the dataset to train the model\n",
        "D_target = Dts[\"Machine failure\"].to_numpy() # get the target column and convert to Numpy array\n",
        "D_feature = Dts.copy().drop([\"Machine failure\", \"Product ID\", \"Type\"], axis=1).to_numpy() # feature is data used to predict the target. Also convert to Numpy array\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "From what I got from my quick research,\n",
        "converting Dataframe to Numpy arrays is not a must.\n",
        "But it's recommended for optimized operations and efficient code execution.\n",
        "That happen because with Numpy arrays\n",
        "you could use Numpy's optimized functions and operations.\n",
        "Note: I also remove some column from the feature because it seems unnecessary\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "Dts # show the dataset"
      ]
    },

        "# Check the correlation of the data by a graphic\n",
        "def heatmap(x, y, size):\n",
        "  fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
        "  # Mapping from columns to integer coordinates\n",
        "  x_labels = [v for v in sorted(x.unique())]\n",
        "  y_labels = [v for v in sorted(y.unique())]\n",
        "  x_to_num = {p[1]:p[0] for p in enumerate(x_labels)}\n",
        "  y_to_num = {p[1]:p[0] for p in enumerate(y_labels)}\n",
        "  size_scale = 300\n",
        "  ax.scatter(\n",
        "    x=x.map(x_to_num),\n",
        "    y=y.map(y_to_num),\n",
        "    s=size * size_scale, # scaling the size\n",
        "    color='c' # c for cyan, I love cyan. my favs\n",
        "  )\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "cor = Dts.corr(numeric_only=True)\n",
        "cor = pd.melt(cor.reset_index(), id_vars='index') # to get pair of arrays for x and y\n",
        "cor.columns = ['x', 'y', 'value']\n",
        "print(\"Correlation between data:\")\n",
        "heatmap(\n",
        "    x=cor['x'],\n",
        "    y=cor['y'],\n",
        "    size=cor['value'].abs()\n",
        ")\n",
        "# I make another graphic to see the column names\n",
        "corr = Dts.corr(numeric_only=True)\n",
        "# visualize the correlation matrix using seaborn with dpecified fig size\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(17,10))\n",
        "sb.heatmap(corr, annot=True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

        "# Training model using logistic regression\n",
        "f2tn, f2ts, t2tn, t2ts = train_test_split(D_feature, D_target, test_size=0.4, random_state=25) # random state 25 cuz I like 25 :3\n",
        "ModelTrained = LogisticRegression(solver='liblinear', max_iter=200)\n",
        "ModelTrained.fit(f2tn, t2tn)"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "# test the result of the test and evaluate the model\n",
        "result_test = ModelTrained.predict(f2ts)\n",
        "\n",
        "evlModel = metrics.confusion_matrix(t2ts, result_test)\n",
        "accuracy = (evlModel[0,0] + evlModel[1,1])/np.sum(evlModel)\n",
        "sensitivity = evlModel[1,1]/(evlModel[1,0]+evlModel[1,1])\n",
        "specificity = evlModel[0,0]/(evlModel[0,0]+evlModel[0,1])\n",
        "precision = evlModel[1,1]/(evlModel[0,1]+evlModel[1,1])\n",
        "print('Accuracy    = {}'.format(np.round(accuracy,3)))\n",
        "print('Sensitvity  = {}'.format(np.round(sensitivity,3)))\n",
        "print('Specificity = {}'.format(np.round(specificity,3)))\n",
        "print('Precision   = {}'.format(np.round(precision,3)))"
      ]
    },
